281
00:12:24,440 --> 00:12:27,440
times delta of k.

282
00:12:27,440 --> 00:12:29,440
Why delta of k?

283
00:12:29,440 --> 00:12:31,440
At k equals 0,

284
00:12:31,440 --> 00:12:33,440
it's not equal to 0.

285
00:12:33,440 --> 00:12:35,440
At k equals anything else,

286
00:12:35,440 --> 00:12:36,440
it is equal to 0.

287
00:12:36,440 --> 00:12:38,440
Now, what is the meaning of this?

288
00:12:38,440 --> 00:12:40,940
This is, the meaning of this is

289
00:12:40,940 --> 00:12:43,440
in the limit of very, very large L.

290
00:12:43,440 --> 00:12:46,440
This becomes a very, very narrow,

291
00:12:46,440 --> 00:12:48,440
very, very high function

292
00:12:48,440 --> 00:12:52,440
whose area is equal to 2 pi.

293
00:12:52,440 --> 00:12:53,440
Okay.

294
00:12:53,440 --> 00:12:55,440
We'll keep that in mind as we go along.

295
00:12:55,440 --> 00:12:57,440
This is called the Dirac delta function,

296
00:12:57,440 --> 00:13:01,440
and we can now say,

297
00:13:01,440 --> 00:13:05,440
let's now go to the limit of very large L.

298
00:13:05,440 --> 00:13:08,440
If we go to the limit of very large L,

299
00:13:08,440 --> 00:13:10,440
in other words, we're making

300
00:13:10,440 --> 00:13:12,440
these intervals progressively smaller and smaller,

301
00:13:12,440 --> 00:13:14,940
we're really approaching the situation that

302
00:13:14,940 --> 00:13:17,440
really does define the Dirac delta function,

303
00:13:17,440 --> 00:13:20,440
then this integral goes all the ways

304
00:13:20,440 --> 00:13:23,440
from minus infinity

305
00:13:23,440 --> 00:13:27,440
to plus infinity.

306
00:13:27,440 --> 00:13:32,440
So, just think of this as a formal prescription

307
00:13:32,440 --> 00:13:36,440
for an integral of e to the i kx,

308
00:13:36,440 --> 00:13:39,440
and the rule is, it gives delta of k,

309
00:13:39,440 --> 00:13:41,440
2 pi times delta of k.

310
00:13:41,440 --> 00:13:44,440
This is equal to 2 pi

311
00:13:44,440 --> 00:13:47,440
times delta of k.

312
00:13:49,440 --> 00:13:52,440
That's something of importance

313
00:13:52,440 --> 00:13:55,440
that when you integrate over a function

314
00:13:55,440 --> 00:13:57,440
of e to the i kx like this,

315
00:13:57,440 --> 00:13:59,440
dx,

316
00:13:59,440 --> 00:14:03,440
you get a Dirac delta function of k.

317
00:14:03,440 --> 00:14:05,940
Let's see if you can guess, supposing

318
00:14:05,940 --> 00:14:08,440
instead of doing the integration over x,

319
00:14:08,440 --> 00:14:10,440
I did an integral over k.

320
00:14:10,440 --> 00:14:12,440
Exactly the same integral,

321
00:14:12,440 --> 00:14:14,440
except it's not at all the same integral,

322
00:14:14,440 --> 00:14:16,440
e to the i kx,

323
00:14:16,440 --> 00:14:18,440
but instead of integrating dx,

324
00:14:18,440 --> 00:14:21,440
I integrate dk.

325
00:14:21,440 --> 00:14:24,440
What must that be?

326
00:14:24,440 --> 00:14:27,440
It's a function of x.

327
00:14:27,440 --> 00:14:29,440
But it's exactly the same structure here,

328
00:14:29,440 --> 00:14:32,440
except I just interchanged x and k, right?

329
00:14:32,440 --> 00:14:35,440
x and k appear symmetrically here,

330
00:14:35,440 --> 00:14:37,440
so if I interchange x and k,

331
00:14:37,440 --> 00:14:38,440
this doesn't change,

332
00:14:38,440 --> 00:14:39,440
but I've changed the integral over k,

333
00:14:39,440 --> 00:14:40,940
I've changed the integral over

334
00:14:40,940 --> 00:14:42,440
x to an integral over k.

335
00:14:42,440 --> 00:14:44,440
So this is now some function of x,

336
00:14:44,440 --> 00:14:47,440
but what is the function?

337
00:14:47,440 --> 00:14:52,440
2 pi times delta of x.

338
00:14:52,440 --> 00:14:55,440
So these are two little observations

339
00:14:55,440 --> 00:14:57,440
that we will see happening,

340
00:14:57,440 --> 00:15:00,440
we'll see their utility

341
00:15:00,440 --> 00:15:03,440
occurring in a number of places.

342
00:15:03,440 --> 00:15:06,440
That's the Dirac delta function.

343
00:15:09,440 --> 00:15:13,440
That's our first little bit of mathematics tonight.

344
00:15:13,440 --> 00:15:18,440
What the hell was that?

345
00:15:18,440 --> 00:15:20,440
Next little bit of mathematics.

346
00:15:20,440 --> 00:15:22,440
I taught you what a ket is.

347
00:15:22,440 --> 00:15:28,440
A ket is a symbolic notation for a quantum state.

348
00:15:28,440 --> 00:15:30,440
I also think I told you...

349
00:15:30,440 --> 00:15:32,440
You didn't use the word ket.

350
00:15:32,440 --> 00:15:33,440
I didn't. What did I use?

351
00:15:33,440 --> 00:15:35,440
I did, I did, I did, I did.

352
00:15:35,440 --> 00:15:37,440
And I told you it was half of a braket.

353
00:15:37,440 --> 00:15:38,440
Yeah.

354
00:15:38,440 --> 00:15:40,440
Yeah, okay.

355
00:15:40,440 --> 00:15:42,440
It's the other half of the braket now

356
00:15:42,440 --> 00:15:44,440
that we want to talk about, the bra,

357
00:15:44,440 --> 00:15:50,440
otherwise known as bra.

358
00:15:50,440 --> 00:15:52,440
These are just notational devices.

359
00:15:52,440 --> 00:15:55,440
For our purposes, these are simply notational devices.

360
00:15:55,440 --> 00:15:57,440
And the question is, when do you use the bra

361
00:15:57,440 --> 00:15:59,440
and when do you use the ket?

362
00:15:59,440 --> 00:16:02,440
For our purposes, we will think of kets

363
00:16:02,440 --> 00:16:05,440
as initial states in a process.

364
00:16:05,440 --> 00:16:08,440
If a process starting with some initial states

365
00:16:08,440 --> 00:16:10,440
is described by some quantum state,

366
00:16:10,440 --> 00:16:15,440
we'll describe the initial state as a ket vector.

367
00:16:17,440 --> 00:16:19,440
Initial.

368
00:16:19,440 --> 00:16:20,440
In.

369
00:16:20,440 --> 00:16:28,440
Final states we will describe by bra vectors.

370
00:16:28,440 --> 00:16:29,440
And when you put a bra

371
00:16:29,440 --> 00:16:30,440
vector next to a ket vector,

372
00:16:30,440 --> 00:16:32,440
you make a bracket.

373
00:16:32,440 --> 00:16:35,440
This is simply a bunch of symbolic manipulation,

374
00:16:35,440 --> 00:16:36,940
but at the end, what

375
00:16:36,940 --> 00:16:38,440
comes out of the symbolic manipulation

376
00:16:38,440 --> 00:16:40,440
are numbers.

377
00:16:40,440 --> 00:16:41,440
Okay?

378
00:16:41,440 --> 00:16:42,440
Numbers.

379
00:16:42,440 --> 00:16:43,440
Numbers.

380
00:16:43,440 --> 00:16:44,440
Experimental numbers.

381
00:16:44,440 --> 00:16:48,440
So I'm going to teach you now some symbolic manipulations.

382
00:16:48,440 --> 00:16:50,440
For every...

383
00:16:50,440 --> 00:16:53,440
Let's go back to the harmonic oscillator.

384
00:16:53,440 --> 00:16:55,440
For the harmonic oscillator,

385
00:16:55,440 --> 00:16:57,440
we characterized the quantum

386
00:16:57,440 --> 00:16:59,440
states of the harmonic oscillator

387
00:16:59,440 --> 00:17:02,440
by occupation numbers, n.

388
00:17:02,440 --> 00:17:06,440
The number of excitations of the harmonic oscillator.

389
00:17:06,440 --> 00:17:07,440
The number of times...

390
00:17:07,440 --> 00:17:09,940
The number of units of energy

391
00:17:09,940 --> 00:17:12,440
that's been put into the harmonic oscillator.

392
00:17:12,440 --> 00:17:14,440
We can also describe it...

393
00:17:14,440 --> 00:17:16,440
That's a ket vector.

394
00:17:16,440 --> 00:17:19,440
That's the ket description of a particular quantum state.

395
00:17:19,440 --> 00:17:21,440
We could also write it

396
00:17:21,440 --> 00:17:23,440
in terms of a bra vector.

397
00:17:23,440 --> 00:17:25,440
So far I haven't told you anything.

398
00:17:25,440 --> 00:17:26,440
I just told you there's two

399
00:17:26,440 --> 00:17:27,440
ways to write the same thing.

400
00:17:27,440 --> 00:17:29,440
You say, what's the difference between them?

401
00:17:29,440 --> 00:17:30,440
Not much.

402
00:17:30,440 --> 00:17:31,440
Okay?

403
00:17:31,440 --> 00:17:33,440
But if we are clever

404
00:17:33,440 --> 00:17:35,440
in our use of this notation,

405
00:17:35,440 --> 00:17:40,440
it will help us do some bookkeeping that's interesting.

406
00:17:40,440 --> 00:17:41,440
All right.

407
00:17:41,440 --> 00:17:43,440
Now, first of all,

408
00:17:43,440 --> 00:17:45,940
there's the notion of the inner product

409
00:17:45,940 --> 00:17:48,440
between a bra vector and a ket vector.

410
00:17:48,440 --> 00:17:50,940
Now, all of this is

411
00:17:50,940 --> 00:17:53,440
in our past quantum mechanics classes,

412
00:17:53,440 --> 00:17:55,440
and I refer you back to it.

413
00:17:55,440 --> 00:17:57,440
We're going to go through it lightning-like tonight.

414
00:17:57,440 --> 00:17:59,440
If I have a ket vector

415
00:17:59,440 --> 00:18:01,440
n and a bra vector m,

416
00:18:01,440 --> 00:18:03,440
I can put them next to each other,

417
00:18:03,440 --> 00:18:05,440
and putting a ket vector in there,

418
00:18:05,440 --> 00:18:06,440
and putting a ket vector next

419
00:18:06,440 --> 00:18:07,440
to a bra vector in this way,

420
00:18:07,440 --> 00:18:09,440
always gives a number.

421
00:18:09,440 --> 00:18:11,440
The ket vectors are abstract things.

422
00:18:11,440 --> 00:18:13,440
The bra vectors are abstract things.

423
00:18:13,440 --> 00:18:15,440
But the product of two of them back to back,

424
00:18:15,440 --> 00:18:18,440
or front to front, I'm not sure which,

425
00:18:18,440 --> 00:18:21,440
in that form, is a number.

426
00:18:21,440 --> 00:18:24,440
This number...

427
00:18:24,440 --> 00:18:26,440
Now, m stands for some quantum state,

428
00:18:26,440 --> 00:18:29,440
the nth quantum state of the oscillator,

429
00:18:29,440 --> 00:18:33,440
and n stands for the nth state of the oscillator.

430
00:18:33,440 --> 00:18:34,440
This number...

431
00:18:34,440 --> 00:18:36,440
This is definition now...

432
00:18:36,440 --> 00:18:38,440
is equal to zero

433
00:18:38,440 --> 00:18:43,440
if m is not equal to n,

434
00:18:43,440 --> 00:18:45,440
and it's equal to one

435
00:18:45,440 --> 00:18:48,440
if m equals n.

436
00:18:48,440 --> 00:18:51,440
So the bra vector and the ket vector,

437
00:18:51,440 --> 00:18:53,440
for the same value of n,

438
00:18:53,440 --> 00:18:55,440
have a product which is one.

439
00:18:55,440 --> 00:18:57,440
It's called the inner product.

440
00:18:57,440 --> 00:18:59,440
The inner product between these two.

441
00:18:59,440 --> 00:19:01,440
It's one if n equals m.

442
00:19:01,440 --> 00:19:02,440
It's zero if n is not equal to m.

443
00:19:02,440 --> 00:19:03,440
Or, to write it, then it's zero.

444
00:19:03,440 --> 00:19:06,440
Or, to write it in a unified form,

445
00:19:06,440 --> 00:19:09,440
we can write it as delta nm,

446
00:19:09,440 --> 00:19:11,440
whose definition is

447
00:19:11,440 --> 00:19:13,440
it's zero unless n equals m,

448
00:19:13,440 --> 00:19:15,440
and one if n is not equal to m.

449
00:19:15,440 --> 00:19:18,440
It's kind of like the Dirac delta function.

450
00:19:18,440 --> 00:19:21,440
It's a discrete form of the Dirac delta function.

451
00:19:21,440 --> 00:19:25,440
All right, this is notational...

452
00:19:25,440 --> 00:19:28,440
This is just notational tricks for things.

453
00:19:28,440 --> 00:19:33,440
Now, let's come to creation and annihilation operators.

454
00:19:33,440 --> 00:19:35,440
What I want to get at before we go further

455
00:19:35,440 --> 00:19:39,440
is how creation and annihilation operators

456
00:19:39,440 --> 00:19:41,440
act on bra vectors.

457
00:19:41,440 --> 00:19:44,440
I've told you how they act on ket vectors,

458
00:19:44,440 --> 00:19:45,940
and I have not told you

459
00:19:45,940 --> 00:19:47,440
how they act on bra vectors.

460
00:19:47,440 --> 00:19:49,440
Now, of course, you can say,

461
00:19:49,440 --> 00:19:51,440
I haven't told you.

462
00:19:51,440 --> 00:19:53,440
In fact, I haven't even told you the rules

463
00:19:53,440 --> 00:19:56,440
which would allow you to deduce how they act.

464
00:19:56,440 --> 00:19:59,440
But I'm going to show you how they act

465
00:19:59,440 --> 00:20:01,440
and then show you why this rule

466
00:20:01,440 --> 00:20:03,440
was particularly nice.

467
00:20:03,440 --> 00:20:07,440
All right, so let's take creation operators first of all.

468
00:20:07,440 --> 00:20:10,440
What does a creation operator do

469
00:20:10,440 --> 00:20:12,940
when it acts on the

470
00:20:12,940 --> 00:20:15,440
nth quantum state of an oscillator?

471
00:20:15,440 --> 00:20:19,440
It multiplies it by square root of n plus one

472
00:20:19,440 --> 00:20:22,440
times the n plus first state.

473
00:20:22,440 --> 00:20:25,440
What about the annihilation?

474
00:20:25,440 --> 00:20:28,440
The annihilation gives you square root of n

475
00:20:28,440 --> 00:20:30,440
times n minus one.

476
00:20:30,440 --> 00:20:32,440
So one of them raises the quantum state,

477
00:20:32,440 --> 00:20:33,440
one of them lowers it,

478
00:20:33,440 --> 00:20:35,440
and then lowers the quantum state,

479
00:20:35,440 --> 00:20:37,440
and in each case they multiply

480
00:20:37,440 --> 00:20:40,440
by the appropriate square root of n.

481
00:20:40,440 --> 00:20:42,440
Now we can ask,

482
00:20:42,440 --> 00:20:44,440
now we're asking for a definition.

483
00:20:44,440 --> 00:20:47,440
This is not a theorem which we want to prove.

484
00:20:47,440 --> 00:20:50,440
This is a definition of how creation

485
00:20:50,440 --> 00:20:52,440
and annihilation operators operate

486
00:20:52,440 --> 00:20:55,440
when they act on bra vectors.

487
00:20:55,440 --> 00:20:59,440
So how shall we take a plus

488
00:20:59,440 --> 00:21:02,440
to act on the nth bra vector?

489
00:21:03,440 --> 00:21:04,940
And I'm going to tell

490
00:21:04,940 --> 00:21:06,440
you now what the rule is.

491
00:21:06,440 --> 00:21:08,940
The rule is that however

492
00:21:08,940 --> 00:21:11,440
it acts on the nth vector,

493
00:21:11,440 --> 00:21:14,440
it gives another vector, another bra vector, of course.

494
00:21:14,440 --> 00:21:16,440
Let's circle that bra vector,

495
00:21:16,440 --> 00:21:18,440
and now take its inner product

496
00:21:18,440 --> 00:21:21,440
with the nth ket vector.

497
00:21:21,440 --> 00:21:23,440
However this acts,

498
00:21:23,440 --> 00:21:24,440
whatever it gives,

499
00:21:24,440 --> 00:21:26,440
it gives another bra vector.

500
00:21:26,440 --> 00:21:27,440
That's the rule.

501
00:21:27,440 --> 00:21:29,440
When an operator acts on a ket vector,

502
00:21:29,440 --> 00:21:30,440
it gives a ket vector.

503
00:21:30,440 --> 00:21:31,440
When it acts on a bra vector,

504
00:21:31,440 --> 00:21:32,440
it gives a bra vector.

505
00:21:32,440 --> 00:21:35,440
And the notation is such

506
00:21:35,440 --> 00:21:37,440
that when an operator acts on a bra vector,

507
00:21:37,440 --> 00:21:39,440
you put the operator to the right

508
00:21:39,440 --> 00:21:41,440
and hit it to the left

509
00:21:41,440 --> 00:21:43,440
when it acts on a ket vector.

510
00:21:43,440 --> 00:21:45,440
So it's a neat notation.

511
00:21:45,440 --> 00:21:49,440
The rule is that you get exactly the same answer

512
00:21:49,440 --> 00:21:52,440
as if you did what?

513
00:21:52,440 --> 00:21:56,440
You applied a plus m.

514
00:21:56,440 --> 00:22:00,440
Allow a plus to act on m

515
00:22:00,440 --> 00:22:05,440
and then take the inner product with n.

516
00:22:05,440 --> 00:22:07,440
See, there's two distinct operations.

517
00:22:07,440 --> 00:22:09,440
However a plus should act on n,

518
00:22:09,440 --> 00:22:10,440
we'd like to find out

519
00:22:10,440 --> 00:22:11,440
how it should act on n,

520
00:22:11,440 --> 00:22:13,440
we're going to define it

521
00:22:13,440 --> 00:22:14,940
so that you get the

522
00:22:14,940 --> 00:22:16,440
same answer for this bra ket

523
00:22:16,440 --> 00:22:19,440
as if you allowed a plus to act on m.

524
00:22:19,440 --> 00:22:21,440
Well, I've given you the rule

525
00:22:21,440 --> 00:22:23,440
for how a plus acts on m,

526
00:22:23,440 --> 00:22:26,440
and then take the inner product with n.

527
00:22:26,440 --> 00:22:29,440
So let's see if we can figure out from this,

528
00:22:29,440 --> 00:22:32,440
from this set of abstract principles

529
00:22:32,440 --> 00:22:34,440
or abstract definitions,

530
00:22:34,440 --> 00:22:37,440
how a plus acts on n.

531
00:22:40,440 --> 00:22:43,440
Let's see.

532
00:22:43,440 --> 00:22:46,440
Let's first take the bottom line here,

533
00:22:46,440 --> 00:22:48,440
the bottom line, let's calculate it.

534
00:22:48,440 --> 00:22:50,440
It's n,

535
00:22:50,440 --> 00:22:52,440
and now a plus acts on m.

536
00:22:52,440 --> 00:22:54,440
What does that give?

537
00:22:54,440 --> 00:22:56,440
Square root of m plus one.

538
00:22:56,440 --> 00:22:58,440
That's a number, we take it outside.

539
00:22:58,440 --> 00:23:00,440
Square root of m plus one,

540
00:23:00,440 --> 00:23:02,440
and then what?

541
00:23:02,440 --> 00:23:04,440
m plus one.

542
00:23:04,440 --> 00:23:08,440
What does this give?

543
00:23:08,440 --> 00:23:11,440
This factor gives zero

544
00:23:11,440 --> 00:23:15,440
unless n is equal to m plus one.

545
00:23:15,440 --> 00:23:19,440
If n is the same as m plus one,

546
00:23:19,440 --> 00:23:21,440
then you get the number

547
00:23:21,440 --> 00:23:23,440
square root of m plus one,

548
00:23:23,440 --> 00:23:25,440
which also happens to be the

549
00:23:25,440 --> 00:23:27,440
square root of n, of course.

550
00:23:27,440 --> 00:23:31,440
So that's one way of calculating what,

551
00:23:31,440 --> 00:23:36,440
that's this over here.

552
00:23:36,440 --> 00:23:39,440
But notice, it only gives an answer,

553
00:23:39,440 --> 00:23:41,440
a non-zero answer,

554
00:23:41,440 --> 00:23:44,440
if this is one unit higher than this.

555
00:23:44,440 --> 00:23:46,440
Sorry.

556
00:23:46,440 --> 00:23:47,440
Yeah.

557
00:23:47,440 --> 00:23:48,440
Sorry.

558
00:23:48,440 --> 00:23:50,940
It only gives an answer if

559
00:23:50,940 --> 00:23:53,440
m is one unit lower than n.

